Durban - Four men who held up a supermarket in Ulundi and killed two KwaZulu-Natal detectives were given life sentences for murder, attempted murder and business robbery in the Mtubatuba High Court. Three years ago, Captain Nkosenye Welcome Ntombela from Ulundi detectives in KwaZulu-Natal were off duty when he and an employee from Phakode Supermarket fell victim to an armed robbery. Four men had entered the supermarket demanding cash. In the process Captain Ntombela was shot dead and his employee was wounded. Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo, spokesperson for the Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation in KZN  (Hawks), said cases of murder, attempted murder and business robbery which were opened at Nongoma Police Station. Mhlongo said the case was allocated to the Hawk’s Richards Bay Serious Organised Crime Investigation. "Members left no stone unturned in their investigation. Two days after the incident Ntokozo Mbatha (29), Siphamandla Mbatha (28), Mzokhona Dlamini (33) and Sifiso Mnyandu (48) were arrested. The four appeared in court several times until they were convicted and sentenced. They were all sentenced to life imprisonment for murder, 15 years for robbery and 10 years for attempted murder. Their sentence will run concurrently. Daily News